# Overhaul Admin Analytics Dashboard with Five Interactive Summary Cards & Sub-Metric Drill-Down Pages

We will implement a premium, institutional analytics dashboard with five (5) primary interactive summary cards featuring embedded chart previews, a shared global filter bar, and drill-down views. All heavy psychometric calculations will run in a separate Worker Thread (`/workers/psychometricWorker.js`) to keep the Express server event loop unblocked.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Heavy Computations in Node.js Worker Thread**:
> To prevent Express blocking, all analytics and collusion checks (O(N²)) will run asynchronously in a Worker Thread.
>
> **UI Styling**:
> We will adhere to the following color tokens:
> - **Emerald Green** (`#10b981`): Safe / Pass Predicted
> - **Amber Yellow** (`#f59e0b`): Warning / Suspicious
> - **Rose Red** (`#f43f5e`): Critical / Danger / High Fatigue
> - **Indigo Blue** (`#6366f1`): Neutral / Volume Stats
> - **Card States**: Crisp white background, subtle borders, soft shadows, and hover animations.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Backend Components

#### [NEW] [psychometricWorker.js](file:///c:/Users/PC/Fia-Cbt-main/fgsigbohocbtv1/workers/psychometricWorker.js)
Create the heavy calculations worker script at root:
1. **Pass Probability Predictor**: Computes weighted likelihood of passing using historical score averages (60%), recent quiz trajectories (30%), and focus factors (10%).
2. **Cognitive Fatigue Index**: Analyzes pacing accuracy drop + speed acceleration comparing the first 25% vs last 25% of question telemetry.
3. **Collusion & Integrity Report**: Calculates incorrect choice matching similarity ($O(N^2)$ pairs analysis) and rapid guessing (<2.5s) / window blur telemetry flags.
4. **Bell Curve Points**: Computes normal distribution curve parameters (mean $\mu$, standard deviation $\sigma$) for scores.
5. **Psychometric Ledger (CTT)**: Computes Item Difficulty ($p$-value), Discrimination Index ($D$), Distractor choices percentage, and Cronbach's Alpha ($\alpha$) for the selected exam.

#### [MODIFY] [routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC/Fia-Cbt-main/fgsigbohocbtv1/server/routes.ts)
1. Import `Worker` from `worker_threads` and instantiate `/workers/psychometricWorker.js`.
2. Update the `/api/analytics` endpoint to fetch Firestore/Drizzle datasets, pass them into the worker, and stream the JSON response back.

